                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-1048" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD HANCOCK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I saw the prisoner in the Broadway, Hammersmith, about seven o'clock, go to a shop and lift a carpet—I followed him round to Mr. Jennings's shop—he put his arm in, but got nothing—he returned, put his arm in again, and took the brushes out—I secured him with them—I found no money on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I had no means of procuring a living.</p>
